# CRITICAL SYSTEM INSTRUCTION: SYSTEM RESTRICTIONS

[RULE: NEVER_USE_GIT_AUTOMATICALLY]
- NEVER execute any Git commands under any circumstances on your own.
- DO NOT run: `git status`, `git diff`, `git add`, `git commit`, `git log`, `git branch`.
- Completely ignore the existence of Git unless the user explicitly tells you: "Выполни команду git...".
- If you need to check if files changed, read the files directly. DO NOT use `git` for tracking changes.

[CONSEQUENCE]
- Breaking this rule will corrupt the workspace. Absolute compliance is mandatory.
